ğŸ“š Semantic Book Recommender
ğŸ“– Overview
The Semantic Book Recommender is a machine learning-powered application that suggests books based on user input. It utilizes natural language processing (NLP) techniques to match books to user queries and ranks them based on emotional tones and categories.
This project is built using Gradio for a user-friendly web interface, LangChain for semantic search, and ChromaDB for vector-based recommendations.

ğŸš€ Features
ğŸ” Semantic Search: Retrieves books based on natural language descriptions.
ğŸ­ Emotion-Based Filtering: Allows users to filter recommendations based on emotional tones (e.g., Happy, Sad, Suspenseful, etc.).
ğŸ“š Category-Based Filtering: Users can refine searches based on book genres.
ğŸ–¼ï¸ Thumbnail Support: Displays book covers alongside recommendations.
ğŸ’» Web Interface: Built with Gradio for an interactive experience.

